    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 1993 Mazda RX-7 FD is a superlative example of rotary engineering, featuring the sequential twin-turbocharged 13B-REW engine in factory-original configuration. The power delivery is seamless, with the secondary turbocharger engaging precisely at 4,500 RPM. Mechanically, the vehicle boasts a pristine cooling system and a Torsen limited-slip differential that remains tight and responsive. The 5-speed manual transmission offers crisp gates with no synchro wear, while the double-wishbone suspension provides the balanced, telepathic handling the FD is renowned for. This mint-condition survivor has been fastidiously maintained, with documented compression scores reflecting a healthy, robust core. A rare opportunity for the purist collector.",
